1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,400
 Well, thank you, Benedict.

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:04,800
 Well, I hope that this message is not so much about us.

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,900
 It's actually going to be a message for you

4
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:11,200
 as we share how we embrace limits

5
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,900
 as well as to break through our limits.

6
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:17,300
 My name is Sydney, and I wish you,

7
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,800
 on behalf of my family who are here,

8
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,800
 a Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year.

9
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,800
 I hope you have all received your Christmas gift.

10
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:28,100
 I received mine.

11
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:29,200
 Yeah.

12
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,100
 Okay, oh, sorry. I showed the logo.

13
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:36,200
 It was purchased very happily by my wife,

14
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:39,500
 given to me, and I gladly received it,

15
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:42,000
 and it was paid through her credit card,

16
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,500
 which is a supplementary card under my account.

17
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:49,200
 And, yes, so she joyously gives.

18
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:52,700
 I gladly receive, and I will pay the bill.

19
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:55,100
 [laughter]

20
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:57,700
 Well, we are coming to the end of the year,

21
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:02,200
 and we just have to learn that there are limits in life,

22
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:08,900
 and time and season are one of the many limits that we encounter.

23
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:13,700
 So today, we are actually sharing on this topic of embracing limits

24
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:16,700
 as well as overcoming limits,

25
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:19,700
 and I call it the gift of limits.

26
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:22,900
 Now, there were research studies that showed

27
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:28,700
 that young children who are playing in the playgrounds

28
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:32,700
 with very clear boundaries, like fences,

29
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:37,200
 they were actually more active and energetic in their play

30
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:43,200
 in these open fields than those without defined boundaries.

31
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:46,900
 So for that purpose, a fenced playground

32
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:50,400
 allowed children to be even more playful.

33
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,700
 They explore all the equipment.

34
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,700
 They were able to interact with peers much better

35
00:01:56,700 --> 00:02:00,400
 than those in unbounded areas,

36
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:05,400
 who they tend to just take it close to the school buildings.

37
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:11,400
 So there's, in that sense, a dual sense of perceived safety

38
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:14,900
 as well as enhanced exploration.

39
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:18,900
 When we know that there's a limit within which it is safe,

40
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:21,900
 we're actually more bold to explore.

41
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:26,900
 Now, the Bible has a lot to talk about boundaries.

42
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:31,900
 The passage I love really well is Psalm 16,

43
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:35,900
 talking about how God keeps us safe,

44
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:38,900
 because in him we took refuge.

45
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:45,900
 In verse 5, he says, "Lord, you alone, you alone

46
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:48,900
 are my portion and my cup.

47
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:51,400
 You make my lot secure.

48
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:55,900
 The boundary lines have fallen for me in pleasant places.

49
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:59,400
 Surely I have a delightful inheritance."

50
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,900
 And my daughter loves that.

51
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:04,400
 I was sharing with her as she travelled back from London to visit us.

52
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:09,400
 We talk about our inheritance distribution, and she loves that.

53
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,900
 (Laughter)

54
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:14,400
 Well, we want to have set boundaries in life,

55
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:18,900
 and we also want to know how to anticipate our future.

56
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:21,900
 Years back when I was practicing in Singapore,

57
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:24,400
 I had a difficult encounter.

58
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,400
 I was a medical profession,

59
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:31,400
 and one of my patients who had a progressive downhill course.

60
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:36,900
 So I was hoping that I would find maybe a certain occasion or chance

61
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:40,900
 to share with him the good news of Jesus.

62
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:44,900
 But as I procrastinated, the chance never really came,

63
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:50,900
 and one odd Saturday afternoon, he just left into a coma.

64
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:56,900
 So in the physical realm, I really find that, well, I'm very, very limited

65
00:03:56,900 --> 00:04:00,900
 in what professionally I can offer.

66
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:03,400
 Very limited options.

67
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:08,400
 But then there may be possibly certain limits that I could break through.

68
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,400
 So I had that stirring in my heart,

69
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:15,400
 but I want to share a word of comfort with his wife,

70
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,900
 who is actually Mandarin-speaking.

71
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:22,400
 So at that time, I tried frantically to call my church pastors,

72
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,900
 ministry leaders, small group leaders.

73
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:29,400
 So everybody is busy on a Saturday and Sunday in church.

74
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:33,900
 And in any event, our church was actually an English-speaking church.

75
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:38,900
 Very few of us speak Mandarin or Chinese really well.

76
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:45,400
 So, well, the pastors, as usual, very wisely advised us,

77
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:49,900
 "Well, why don't you go ahead and share some comforting words with the family?"

78
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:53,400
 So I frantically grabbed my wife,

79
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:57,400
 and we went together to the hospital to minister to the wife.

80
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:03,400
 So that was my very first time ministering to someone in Mandarin.

81
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:07,900
 So that was a breakthrough for me, despite all the limitations.

82
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:11,400
 Of course, down the road, we moved back to Hong Kong.

83
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:16,900
 And all these 18 years whereby we have been worshipping in the Vine Church,

84
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:21,400
 we see the mighty hands of God moving in amongst us.

85
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:26,400
 But almost 10 years ago, while we were still very much an English-speaking church,

86
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,900
 we began to run Cantonese Alpha.

87
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:35,400
 And that was one of the first Cantonese Alpha retreats in the last act,

88
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:40,900
 where you may be able to see some familiar faces.

89
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:48,900
 Well, I believe that God has somehow divinely brought me and my wife, Pastor Vivian,

90
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:52,900
 to serve in the Vine.

91
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:56,900
 And over the years, we saw the birth of both the Cantonese

92
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:59,900
 as well as the Mandarin-speaking communities.

93
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:05,900
 And what started as a small home group of 10, 20 people

94
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:10,900
 became a community of like 60, 70 people.

95
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:16,900
 But more importantly, we do believe that there is more to come.

96
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:18,900
 There is more to come.

97
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:24,900
 Well, in fact, my son's middle school last time in Singapore had this school motto.

98
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:29,900
 It's Anglo-Chinese school, Yinghua Zhonghe.

99
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:36,900
 Well, the school motto is something like this, "The best is yet to be."

100
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:41,900
 But it's followed by, "To God be the glory."

101
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:47,900
 The best is yet to be when it's in line with God being honoured and glorified.

102
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:49,900
 So what is this more?

103
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:54,900
 We've embraced the River Vision for the past six, seven years.

104
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:59,900
 Well, Yundong was in fact birthed as part of this vision,

105
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:02,900
 and the dream came true three to four years ago.

106
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:09,900
 I must say it was one of the greatest joy of my serving in the Vine all these years

107
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:14,900
 to see the Vine Yundong blossom and continue to grow.

108
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:21,900
 But I pray that this will continue to inspire us to see that we are actually something.

109
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:26,900
 We are part of an even greater plan that is unfolding.

110
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:32,900
 So in fact, some of you have heard from the announcements, from Wan Chai, from here,

111
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:40,900
 that the leadership of the Vine, myself and Vivian, are sensing a call for us to move out

112
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:51,900
 and to plant a fresh kind of missional Vine church to serve the future northern metropolis area of Hong Kong.

113
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:53,900
 Northern metropolis.

114
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:58,900
 By the way, Yundong is actually part of the northern metropolis.

115
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:07,900
 Now this is very much in line with the vision of the River Initiative that we want to carry on.

116
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:18,900
 But we do want to focus on sharing this love of Christ with Chinese speakers,

117
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:25,900
 Cantonese and Mandarin included, in a way that will encourage real and deep spiritual growth

118
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:29,900
 and to build loving, caring, Christ-centered communities.

119
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:34,900
 So you may want to ask, why? Why northern metropolis?

120
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:41,900
 Well to start with, the very motto of the Vine is to bear fruits.

121
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:49,900
 Every branch that does bear fruit, he prunes so that it will be even more fruitful.

122
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:57,900
 So the Vine is destined, you are destined, to bear more fruits in your life.

123
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:00,900
 But then still, the question, why northern metropolis?

124
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:05,900
 Well as you all know, that it will become the fastest growing areas.

125
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:11,900
 And the area actually includes the Shanghai, Fanning, Yundong, Tianshui,

126
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:15,900
 but then also new zones like Kutong and Shantin.

127
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:21,900
 Now over the next decade, it's estimated that there will be one million new residents moving in,

128
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:25,900
 bringing the total population to up to 2 or 2.5 million.

129
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:33,900
 There will be new families, professionals, people from Hong Kong who are reallocated from their original residences,

130
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:39,900
 and of course some other new residents from mainland China.

131
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:45,900
 So yet, on this new area of development, there may be very few churches.

132
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:51,900
 Yes, we have Yundong, and we have other churches, but there are never enough churches.

133
00:09:51,900 --> 00:10:01,900
 Some places are in fact a blank state, and that would be a great and tremendous opportunity for the gospel to take root and to bear fruits.

134
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:06,900
 Well, lots of work for Yundong, as well as the new church plant.

135
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:11,900
 And there will be new neighbours, people who have as yet to know Jesus,

136
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:17,900
 but they are loved by Jesus as much as we are loved by Jesus.

137
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:27,900
 Vine, Vine Wan Chai has this restoration ministry where Vivian is heading.

138
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:35,900
 It's interesting that while they are offering classes, originally in English, then it was extended to Cantonese,

139
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:41,900
 we saw the hand of God moving into Mandarin-based ministry.

140
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:46,900
 So for this outreach to especially Chinese-speaking people, including both the Cantonese speakers,

141
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:53,900
 as well as the Mandarin speakers, we were able to testify and witness the transformation of lives.

142
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:58,900
 People are inviting their friends, their families to come to know Jesus,

143
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:05,900
 and we also even see reconciliation between the Cantonese and the Mandarin speakers.

144
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:11,900
 In fact, when we were travelling in New Zealand doing a new video series on restoration,

145
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:18,900
 we actually have a special purpose in mind because we want to translate the English-based videos

146
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:27,900
 to become with Mandarin subtitle, with a crew of people who are actually from China to help us with the production.

147
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:35,900
 So we can see, well, there will be new ways that we will be able to reach out to our Chinese-speaking friends.

148
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:44,900
 In Mark 4, it records a mini-revival in the small town of Kapok Noon,

149
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:54,900
 where Jesus and the initial team really ministered to the people, healed the sick, cast out the demons, and performed miracles.

150
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:59,900
 But then Jesus said to his disciples, "Let us go over to the other side."

151
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:02,900
 What does it mean to go to the other side?

152
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:08,900
 Well, where they are based, they have a comfortable zone to continue to grow and minister.

153
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:14,900
 Where they are moving on to is a new and could be potentially hostile area,

154
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:21,900
 a lot more dominated by Gentiles according to the geographic distribution.

155
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:24,900
 But Jesus called them to venture.

156
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:32,900
 Likewise, our calling is to cross over, to go further, to step into a new land, uncharted areas.

157
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:42,900
 Do we dare to believe that God is leading the vine and all of us here to these kind of uncharted areas of ministry

158
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:46,900
 as part of God's kingdom's advancement?

159
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:51,900
 But then we want to narrow our reaching out to local Cantonese speakers,

160
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:55,900
 as well as Mandarin speakers who are settling into new land.

161
00:12:55,900 --> 00:13:05,900
 And then we want to start now, that we would be able to have a base somewhere along what we call the East Rail Line

162
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:11,900
 that could include anywhere from Tai Wai, Sha Tin, Tai Po, Fan Neng, or Sheung Shui,

163
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:18,900
 as a base so that we would be able to move into the northern metropolis in due time.

164
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:23,900
 Well, in fact, our family have made a small boat move.

165
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:26,900
 So I used to live on the Hong Kong Island side.

166
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:31,900
 In fact, if I'm to go to work, it took me about three minutes.

167
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:34,900
 Yeah, because I lived in the hospital quarter.

168
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:40,900
 So I would take a lift, I walk, I take another lift, then I'll be in my workplace.

169
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:47,900
 So as I moved, I typically would take around 40 to 50 minutes to go to work on a daily basis.

170
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:54,900
 So every night I hope that I would not be caught by anyone from the hospital, just in case I need to travel back.

171
00:13:54,900 --> 00:14:03,900
 But now that we are living in the new territories, we are 20 minutes from the northern metropolis.

172
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:14,900
 So this morning I took 20 minutes, I passed by Tai Po, Fan Neng, Sheung Shui, Koo Tung, here I am in Yunnan.

173
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:18,900
 So that allows tremendous possibility.

174
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:23,900
 But the most important of all is we want to live amongst the people they want to serve.

175
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:25,900
 Yeah, as simple as that.

176
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:33,900
 Well, we just pray that as we commit and as we avail ourselves, God will honour our commitment.

177
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:38,900
 Notwithstanding that we do have our own limitations.

178
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:48,900
 Well, the future church plant may be starting small, but as we plant the seed, may God continue to grow lives.

179
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,900
 Are we the best person to serve?

180
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:56,900
 Well, we don't really have too much connections with local churches here in Hong Kong.

181
00:14:56,900 --> 00:15:02,900
 We have very little understanding of the religious sentiments in Hong Kong or in China.

182
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:10,900
 We didn't even have the full Christian vocabulary or prayer language in Cantonese or in Mandarin to start with.

183
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:15,900
 And our Mandarin has much room to improve.

184
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:25,900
 But looking back now, I realise that these limits are exactly where God was inviting us to surrender.

185
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:34,900
 What I saw as a limitation, God wants us to embrace as an invitation.

186
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:38,900
 Limitation. Invitation.

187
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:46,900
 But the invitation is for his presence to lead, his strength to see us through, and to make known his heart for the Chinese.

188
00:15:46,900 --> 00:15:52,900
 Not by our own ability, but by his calling and by his grace.

189
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:58,900
 And now as we step into this next uncharted chapter as a church,

190
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:04,900
 where we want to reach out to the Chinese population in new context, in a new era,

191
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:13,900
 not from a place of confidence, but from a place of love, of authenticity and vulnerability.

192
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:20,900
 Well, God's kingdom, of course, is growing in all fronts, and divine's work is not only limited to one language.

193
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:31,900
 But embracing our own limitations, we actually decided that we would stay focused and narrow down to just the Chinese speakers.

194
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:36,900
 So that brought us to the discernment of knowing our own limits.

195
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,900
 So there are two kinds of limits.

196
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:45,900
 Well, we have to ask, what are the limits that I have to submit joyfully as God's invitation to trust him?

197
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:52,900
 On the other hand, we may also need to ask, what are the limits that I need to push through by faith,

198
00:16:52,900 --> 00:17:00,900
 so that others can see him and I can be the very instrument to have him manifest in our life.

199
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:13,900
 So on this end, while we accept, embrace limits, those limits actually protect us, keep us humble, and help us grow in wisdom.

200
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:20,900
 Say, for example, in my own situation, I still got to work to support the family.

201
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:25,900
 Yeah, sorry. You are on your own most of the time in ministry.

202
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:34,900
 My work as a medical professional is demanding and often draining, both physically and emotionally.

203
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:39,900
 And that I myself have a medical condition that would need regular treatment.

204
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:46,900
 And that a bivocational ministry is a brand new entity in divine.

205
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:52,900
 Well, we all need to be aware of our own limits and need to embrace them.

206
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:54,900
 So you may want to consider your own limits.

207
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:58,900
 So what are the limits of your personality and temperament?

208
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:05,900
 I'm an introvert and does not naturally connect well with new friends.

209
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:07,900
 What are the limits of my current season?

210
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:10,900
 So some of us may need to look after younger kids.

211
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:15,900
 Others, they may have to look after their senior parents.

212
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:23,900
 Well, we have physical, emotional challenges or external crisis that could alter our own life.

213
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:31,900
 And there are even seasons whereby we just face difficulties or even struggles in our financial situation.

214
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:36,900
 There may be seasons that you need to be intensively working or studying.

215
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:45,900
 And yet there are other seasons that you need to step back from responsibilities and grieve a significant loss.

216
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:52,900
 What are the limits of your physical, emotional, and intellectual capacities?

217
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:59,900
 Well, but we just need to know all our capacities are also a God-given limit.

218
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:03,900
 I need time to read, to pray, and to be alone.

219
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:09,900
 I cannot work or pray for five or six hours like I used to be able to.

220
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:12,900
 What are the limits of our time?

221
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:16,900
 Well, all I know is that we only have one life to live.

222
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:21,900
 But we can't do all the things that we want to do.

223
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:31,900
 However, the scripture reminds us of important examples whereby we need to learn to embrace the limits.

224
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:40,900
 It was within the limits of the five barley loaves and two fish that Jesus was revealed as the bread of life.

225
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:51,900
 It was within the limits of Moses who was slow of speech and 80 years of age who had led millions out of Egypt.

226
00:19:51,900 --> 00:20:02,900
 We remember the widow who gave her all, the two corns, because of the limits of her financial resources.

227
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:08,900
 But in Jesus' eyes, she has given far more than all the others.

228
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:16,900
 So if these biblical heroes had rebelled against their own limits, their limited resources, their limited abilities,

229
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:26,900
 or limited family situation, they would have missed out what God wanted to do in and through them.

230
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:34,900
 So I would say limits are often God's blessing and gifts in disguise.

231
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:38,900
 Limits are just God's gifts in disguise.

232
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:43,900
 We only see a very, very small part of God's plan at any point in time.

233
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:50,900
 What he does in and through our limits is more than we could ever accomplish in our own strength.

234
00:20:50,900 --> 00:21:00,900
 One of the indicators that we are maturing spiritually is that we can live joyfully within our God-given limits.

235
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:04,900
 I'm learning to embrace mine in this new season of serving.

